LAGOS  – The National Pension Commission (PenCom) has directed the Pension Funds Administrators (PFAs) to begin the implementation of the Pension Enhancement for retirees. According to the Commission, the directive is for the second edition of the pension enhancement exercise for retirees on Programmed Withdrawal mode of retirement. Mr Peter Agahowa, Head, Corporate Communications at PenCom, in a statement ,added that the pension enhancement is for Contributory Pension Scheme (CPS) retirees who have accumulated significant growth in their Retirement Savings Accounts (RSAs) and had retired between July 2007 and December 2017. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network He noted that the Commission advised the retirees referred to above, by this notice, to contact their respective Pension Fund Administrators (PFAs) to confirm their eligibility and complete requisite documentations. Part of the statement read “The National Pension Commission hereby informs the general public that all Pension Fund Administrators (PFAs) have been directed to implement the second edition of the pension enhancement exercise for retirees on Programmed Withdrawal mode of retirement. “The pension enhancement is for Contributory Pension Scheme (CPS) retirees who have accumulated significant growth in their Retirement Savings Accounts (RSAs) and had retired between July 2007 and December 2017. Accordingly, the retirees referred to above are by this notice advised to contact their respective Pension Fund Administrators (PFAs) to confirm their eligibility and complete requisite documentations.”